text: Had dinner there. A party of 6 pax and spent about $130. We ordered the claypot fish soup (which was the bill of the cost), marmite venison, pork ribs, mixed vegetables, san loh hor fun. Quality of the dishes were good and I think the quite innovative … marmite venison??!! Interesting.

Food: Ordered fish head steamboat, prawn paste chicken, sambal kang kong, and prawn omelette. The soup is nice and worth the price.
Service: Normal
Atmosphere: Hot and humid coffeeshop

Very shocked at how small and little the portion is given the price at $7. When I can get better, bigger portion and maybe even with an egg at other places.
Unhappy with the portion x price.
Taste wise is not bad.
But, sorry not sorry, too disappointed to go back again.

Located at newly renovated  coffee shop at blk 273 bukit batok..

$13 for asam fish head (promotion price) for this month.. "Ang go li" fish head taste not bad..

(Went bad 2weeks later n was told.. No more at promotion price.. $25 for dining in???) But banner still showing promotion leh..

Prawn paste chicken.. $12 for a plate of 8 mid wings.. Also not bad..

Decent taste.. (Not going again le)
Excellent seafood place ; affordable and the red snapper is superb la ; don’t mind the photo , we eat already :-)
